commit.message: CI: test with GAP 4.13; test with mininimal set of packages loaded
Update .gitignore
Version 4.7.3
Fix GH Actions setup
Updated email address.
PackageInfo.g: link to Mathjax manual by default
Remove superfluous .release file
CI: tweak concurrency limiting
CI: switch to new action names, simplify doc job
Switch CI to use GitHub Actions
Clean up .codecov.yml

Fixed a bug in the 3-argument version of 'PartitionsIntoResidueClasses'. -- If the length of the partitions to be computed was smaller than the biggest prime specified in the third argument, the third argument was just ignored.

Change IsZ_pi from a property to a category

This seems correct, as there were no real methods to compute it. Also,
it is very similar to IsIntegers, which is also a category.

This makes a so-called "hidden" implication created by DeclareProperty
explicit, thereby resolving a bunch of warnings that show up if one
starts the upcoming GAP 4.11 with the `-N` command line option, and then
loads this package.

For some information on the background of this, see also
<https://github.com/gap-system/gap/issues/1649> and
<https://github.com/gap-system/gap/issues/2336>

Travis: fix RCWA testing; test against GAP 4.11

The line that was supposed to run the test of the latest RCWA git version
using the latest resclasses git version actually run the RCWA tests against
whatever version of resclasses was bundled with GAP.
Set version to dev
Remove utils for preparing the package for distribution
Version 4.7.2
Let AutoDoc generate manual title page
Restrict \< methods for list and ring

Add .release file, tweak Travis integration

The .release file ensures that some stuff we don't want to see in the
tarball are removed by ReleaseTools when creating the tarball.

The Travis changes are purely janitorial.
Add GPL2 LICENSE file
PackageInfo.g: add License field

ci: also run tests for latest RCWA

This should help catch changes to resclasses that break RCWA.
Set version to 4.7.1dev
Test compat with GAP 4.9, 4.10 and master
travis: switch to using pkg-ci-scripts

Stop using (Un)HideGlobalVariables

These functions are marked as obsolete in GAP master, which causes
warnings to appear when using them. Calling them was only used for
tests, and I could not see why. So it seems reasonable to disable this.
Add \- method for a ring element and a ring

Restrict filters for two \- methods

The new filters match the info string of the methods.

Resolves point 6 of https://github.com/gap-system/gap/issues/2164
Set up Travis & Codecov
